Show us how you move back and forth while doing that move.

238
00:07:52,521 --> 00:07:53,590
Like how a lead role shows up on and leaves the stage.

239
00:07:53,591 --> 00:07:54,591
Here we go.

240
00:07:55,351 --> 00:07:56,360
Like a lead role.

241
00:07:56,361 --> 00:07:57,990
(The two funny musical actors have amazing chemistry together.)

242
00:07:57,991 --> 00:07:58,991
That's amazing.

243
00:08:00,631 --> 00:08:02,800
- That was great.
- We do whatever we're asked to do.

244
00:08:02,801 --> 00:08:03,801
(Shocked)

245
00:08:04,301 --> 00:08:05,630
(Sung Rok has overcome his trauma caused by Ho Dong.)

246
00:08:05,631 --> 00:08:07,970
- Sung Rok is very tall.
- Exactly.

247
00:08:07,971 --> 00:08:09,040
- I heard Gun Woo was...
- Exactly.

248
00:08:09,041 --> 00:08:10,100
close to Hee Chul.

249
00:08:10,101 --> 00:08:11,940
You have visited Hee Chul's house? Tell us your story.

250
00:08:11,941 --> 00:08:14,170
- I even saw Gun Woo's underwear.
- What?

251
00:08:14,171 --> 00:08:15,680
- I went to his house-warming party.
- A house-warming party?

252
00:08:15,681 --> 00:08:16,910
Doesn't that mean they're really close?

253
00:08:16,911 --> 00:08:20,110
Gun Woo, why did you meet him and become friends with him?

254
00:08:20,111 --> 00:08:22,220
We go to the same gym.

255
00:08:22,221 --> 00:08:23,650
- Do you two work out?
- Hee Chul...

256
00:08:23,651 --> 00:08:24,680
- has been working out.
- Do you work out?

257
00:08:24,681 --> 00:08:26,820
- Hee Chul, did you drink yesterday?
- No.

258
00:08:26,821 --> 00:08:28,250
- So they met through a show.
- Why is your face so red?

259
00:08:28,251 --> 00:08:29,260
- I don't drink these days.
- His face is red?

260
00:08:29,261 --> 00:08:30,490
It's because I'm not wearing makeup.

261
00:08:30,491 --> 00:08:31,860
While I was putting on makeup,

262
00:08:31,861 --> 00:08:33,891
I heard we'd have three male guests. So I wiped it off.

263
00:08:35,131 --> 00:08:36,930
- You removed your makeup?
- I felt like it was a waste.

264
00:08:36,931 --> 00:08:38,030
Is that why your face is red?

265
00:08:38,031 --> 00:08:40,100
Yes, because I rubbed my face hard to remove my makeup.

266
00:08:40,101 --> 00:08:42,200
- I rubbed it so hard.
- No wonder.

267
00:08:42,201 --> 00:08:43,470
Why did Hee Chul go to your house-warming party?

268
00:08:43,471 --> 00:08:46,340
- Why did he go there?
- We met on another TV show...

269
00:08:46,341 --> 00:08:48,740
- where I was moving to a new house.
- What TV show?

270
00:08:48,741 --> 00:08:50,810
Why didn't you just tell us? You can say it was "Mom's Diary."

271
00:08:50,811 --> 00:08:53,210
- On "Mom's Diary..."
- Why didn't you just tell us?

272
00:08:53,211 --> 00:08:55,820
They filmed me moving into my new house for "Mom's Diary."

273
00:08:55,821 --> 00:08:57,980
He came to see me that day.

274
00:08:57,981 --> 00:08:59,190
He gave me a house-warming gift...

275
00:08:59,191 --> 00:09:00,450
and helped me with the move.

276
00:09:00,451 --> 00:09:01,451
- Really?
- When I met him...

277
00:09:01,452 --> 00:09:03,160
I felt this when I met him on his moving day.

278
00:09:03,161 --> 00:09:05,390
He seemed totally different from the way he did in "The Glory."

279
00:09:05,391 --> 00:09:07,830
- He wore dreadlocks in the drama.
- Exactly.

280
00:09:07,831 --> 00:09:09,860
(He exuded an evil charisma, playing Son Myeong Oh in the drama.)

281
00:09:09,861 --> 00:09:11,000
- That's right.
- He seemed so different then.

282
00:09:11,001 --> 00:09:12,270
- He has such kind eyes now.
- He looks so different now.

283
00:09:12,271 --> 00:09:13,670
- Gun Woo played the role?
- You should be careful...

284
00:09:13,671 --> 00:09:15,000
Gun Woo, be wary of him.

285
00:09:15,001 --> 00:09:16,300
- He's obsessed with actors.
- He looks like a different person.

286
00:09:16,301 --> 00:09:17,570
He loves actors so much...

287
00:09:17,571 --> 00:09:19,440
- that he treats them to a meal.
- Me?

288
00:09:19,441 --> 00:09:21,410
- Don't you?
- He's not like you, though.

289
00:09:21,411 --> 00:09:23,310
- Everyone knows that.
- Aren't you...

290
00:09:23,311 --> 00:09:25,340
Aren't you the one who loves to eat with actors?

291
00:09:25,341 --> 00:09:26,910
- That's right.
- Aren't you famous for that?

292
00:09:26,911 --> 00:09:28,180
Tell us why.

293
00:09:28,181 --> 00:09:29,580
- I've never eaten with any actors.
- I mean...

294
00:09:29,581 --> 00:09:31,480
- That's right.
- Actors don't get to see him often.

295
00:09:31,481 --> 00:09:33,250
And he can be funny when you first meet him.

296
00:09:33,251 --> 00:09:34,390
- That's right.
- Yeong Cheol...

297
00:09:34,391 --> 00:09:35,990
But imagine you meet him over and over again.

298
00:09:35,991 --> 00:09:38,420
- Soon...
- He used to treat me to a meal.

299
00:09:38,421 --> 00:09:41,161
Sang Hun, I treated you a lot after you became an actor.

300
00:09:41,691 --> 00:09:42,900
After he became an actor?

301
00:09:42,901 --> 00:09:45,801
Right. You didn't even spare me a glance before that.

302
00:09:46,501 --> 00:09:48,430
Actually, I made a lot of good memories with Yeong Cheol.

303
00:09:48,431 --> 00:09:50,540
- I'm close to him and Sung Hwa.
- Right.

304
00:09:50,541 --> 00:09:53,141
Chung Sung Hwa, Yeong Cheol, and I...

305
00:09:53,571 --> 00:09:55,881
went camping together.

306
00:09:56,311 --> 00:09:58,640
Yeong Cheol said he had never set up a tent before.

307
00:09:58,641 --> 00:10:00,111
That was okay.

308
00:10:00,611 --> 00:10:03,020
But then, he gave us orders like moving the tent...

309
00:10:03,021 --> 00:10:05,380
- to another spot.
- There's a lot to do when camping.

310
00:10:05,381 --> 00:10:07,150
- We moved the tent as he asked.
- Where is this going?

311
00:10:07,151 --> 00:10:08,690
- He acted like a prince.
- We did it for him.

312
00:10:08,691 --> 00:10:11,690
When you go camping, your food options are quite limited.

313
00:10:11,691 --> 00:10:13,590
- People usually eat ramyeon...
- Right.

314
00:10:13,591 --> 00:10:14,930
- or pork belly...
- Or some meat.

315
00:10:14,931 --> 00:10:16,331
- with some kimchi.
- That's right.

316
00:10:16,801 --> 00:10:19,800
He asked me to make sausage fritters,

317
00:10:19,801 --> 00:10:21,471
with sausages dipped in egg wash and pan-fried.

318
00:10:21,931 --> 00:10:23,070
- He asked you for it?
- He asked me for it.

319
00:10:23,071 --> 00:10:24,300
- At a campsite?
- My gosh.

320
00:10:24,301 --> 00:10:26,540
- He asked me to make fritters...
- How do you do that at a campsite?

321
00:10:26,541 --> 00:10:27,541
I mean...

322
00:10:28,041 --> 00:10:29,840
You mean, those pink sausages?

323
00:10:29,841 --> 00:10:32,810
- The fritters made with them?
- He asked me to make fritters.

324
00:10:32,811 --> 00:10:34,880
- That's obnoxious.
- How annoying is that?

325
00:10:34,881 --> 00:10:37,720
You guys just don't understand. Sang Hun is such a great cook.

326
00:10:37,721 --> 00:10:39,820
- How do you do it at a campsite?
- We were camping.

327
00:10:39,821 --> 00:10:41,550
No matter how well you cook,

328
00:10:41,551 --> 00:10:43,890
it's too much work to make fritters at a campsite.

329
00:10:43,891 --> 00:10:44,960
- You eat simple food like ramyeon.
- I know, but still...

330
00:10:44,961 --> 00:10:46,760
On top of that, it turned out we set up our tent...

331
00:10:46,761 --> 00:10:49,261
- on rocky ground.
- There were rocks under it.

332
00:10:49,901 --> 00:10:51,630
As the oldest in the group,

333
00:10:51,631 --> 00:10:53,100
he could've taken the uncomfortable spot.

334
00:10:53,101 --> 00:10:54,971
But he was like, "I can't sleep on rocky ground."

335
00:10:55,431 --> 00:10:57,371
I said, "Sang Hun, take the rocky spot."

336
00:10:57,741 --> 00:10:59,240
Since the ground was on a slight incline,

337
00:10:59,241 --> 00:11:01,611
- I made him sleep over rocks.
- he kept sliding toward me.

338
00:11:01,941 --> 00:11:04,480
He doesn't deserve to be treated as an older one.

339
00:11:04,481 --> 00:11:07,610
I once appeared on Jang Hoon's show.

340
00:11:07,611 --> 00:11:09,850
We slept at a house that was almost falling apart.

341
00:11:09,851 --> 00:11:11,521
Even Jang Hoon, a clean freak,

342
00:11:11,651 --> 00:11:12,920
was considerate of me.

343
00:11:12,921 --> 00:11:14,420
He said I should sleep in a better room.

344
00:11:14,421 --> 00:11:16,521
He let me use the nicest room and laid out the beddings for me.

345
00:11:17,121 --> 00:11:18,560
I mean, my gosh. How could he...

346
00:11:18,561 --> 00:11:19,930
complain about rocks under the tent?

347
00:11:19,931 --> 00:11:22,631
You were on a TV show, but they were not.

348
00:11:23,461 --> 00:11:25,200
- Oh, that's right.
- Thank you, Soo Geun.

349
00:11:25,201 --> 00:11:26,400
- If we hadn't been on a TV show...
- He wouldn't have done that.

350
00:11:26,401 --> 00:11:28,070
- He'd never sleep in a tent.
- He'd take a room with a bed.

351
00:11:28,071 --> 00:11:29,641
- Thank you so much, Soo Geun.
- Who would volunteer to do that?

352
00:11:30,041 --> 00:11:31,340
He can't even stretch his legs in a tent.

353
00:11:31,341 --> 00:11:33,410
By any chance,

354
00:11:33,411 --> 00:11:35,171
has Yeong Cheol ever asked you...

355
00:11:35,311 --> 00:11:38,140
to help him get cast in a musical...

356
00:11:38,141 --> 00:11:40,050
when he met you?

357
00:11:40,051 --> 00:11:42,151
I felt that. He made it obvious.

358
00:11:42,381 --> 00:11:44,251
- He keeps singing in front of us.
- Me?

359
00:11:45,991 --> 00:11:48,820
- I really hate to hear him sing.
- Singing is just one of my habits.

360
00:11:48,821 --> 00:11:50,160
- But he won't stop singing.
- Here's why I asked you that.

361
00:11:50,161 --> 00:11:52,761
When Sang Hun was dancing,

362
00:11:52,831 --> 00:11:55,131
I saw Yeong Cheol dance, copying his moves.

363
00:11:55,291 --> 00:11:57,530
That made me think...

364
00:11:57,531 --> 00:11:59,270
that maybe his real dream was to perform in a musical.

365
00:11:59,271 --> 00:12:01,270
- Sing "Rebecca" for us.
- It's a little bit...

366
00:12:01,271 --> 00:12:03,200
- As a matter of fact...
- I've sung it too many times.

367
00:12:03,201 --> 00:12:06,810
A musical actor needs his own unique characteristics...

368
00:12:06,811 --> 00:12:08,711
like charisma or cuteness.

369
00:12:08,841 --> 00:12:11,141
But Yeong Cheol is a bit annoying.

370
00:12:11,981 --> 00:12:14,280
- A musical actor needs charisma.
- I'm over-the-top.

371
00:12:14,281 --> 00:12:16,020
- I lack charisma.
- Right.

372
00:12:16,021 --> 00:12:18,220
- And I'm an annoying type.
- He's not charming in that way.

373
00:12:18,221 --> 00:12:20,991
What's even funnier is that Ho Dong's pride is hurt.

374
00:12:21,151 --> 00:12:22,660
Whenever he asked Yeong Cheol to sing "Rebecca,"

375
00:12:22,661 --> 00:12:24,290
he would sing it right away, but just earlier,

376
00:12:24,291 --> 00:12:27,260
he refused to sing it. Ho Dong is sulky now.

377
00:12:27,261 --> 00:12:28,661
Who are you to refrain yourself?

378
00:12:29,331 --> 00:12:32,501
- I sang "Rebecca..."
- You must always be too much!

379
00:12:32,831 --> 00:12:34,571
- You must always be over-the-top!
- But "Rebecca..."

380
00:12:34,631 --> 00:12:35,840
Just like I do.

381
00:12:35,841 --> 00:12:37,500
- I started dancing right away.
- Watch him and learn.

382
00:12:37,501 --> 00:12:39,001
- But...
- Sang Hun, jump!

383
00:12:39,241 --> 00:12:40,711
One, two, three, four.

384
00:12:40,771 --> 00:12:43,510
- Jump!
- See? I do whatever I'm asked.

385
00:12:43,511 --> 00:12:46,381
- I sang it when Choi Jung Won came.
- He usually sings right away.

386
00:12:46,551 --> 00:12:48,411
- I think you're incredible.
- But he refused to sing earlier.

387
00:12:48,611 --> 00:12:49,720
You're amazing.

388
00:12:49,721 --> 00:12:52,150
That's why you can't be a musical actor. I do it right away.

389
00:12:52,151 --> 00:12:54,521
(The age of the cathedrals has come)

390
00:12:55,551 --> 00:12:56,590
(The unlimited energy of the musical scene never gets tired.)

391
00:12:56,591 --> 00:12:58,290
See? I danced right away. You should've started singing...

392
00:12:58,291 --> 00:13:01,390
- Now, Gun Woo, the youngest...
- He should've sung.

393
00:13:01,391 --> 00:13:02,830
- Son Myeong Oh...
- Right. Bring it to me...

394
00:13:02,831 --> 00:13:04,261
before anyone asks you to do things like that.

395
00:13:04,401 --> 00:13:05,600
- Show us your charisma.
- He looks totally different now.

396
00:13:05,601 --> 00:13:07,670
- He looks like a different person.
- He looks so kind.

397
00:13:07,671 --> 00:13:09,200
He looks so different from his character Son Myeong Oh.

398
00:13:09,201 --> 00:13:11,741
- He has a totally different vibe.
- Exactly.

399
00:13:11,841 --> 00:13:14,040
- He didn't look like this.
- Is there a famous quote?

400
00:13:14,041 --> 00:13:16,441
- You swear in the elevator.
- He also has a beautiful smile.

401
00:13:16,611 --> 00:13:18,211
What do you say in the elevator in that scene?

402
00:13:18,541 --> 00:13:19,811
- In the elevator? Oh, right.
- Yes.

403
00:13:19,951 --> 00:13:21,751
- "Hurry up and get out?"
- Reenact the scene.

404
00:13:21,911 --> 00:13:23,451
- "I said I liked you."
- "Which floor?"

405
00:13:23,951 --> 00:13:27,051
(In this iconic scene, he confesses his love in a totally unusual way.)

406
00:13:27,351 --> 00:13:29,661
(I said I liked you!)

407
00:13:30,021 --> 00:13:31,361
- "Son Myeong Oh."
- Yes?

408
00:13:31,591 --> 00:13:34,331
"Why did you call me in the elevator?"

409
00:13:34,691 --> 00:13:36,960
- What's that?
- He didn't watch "The Glory."

410
00:13:36,961 --> 00:13:38,260
- What are you talking about?
- He didn't watch "The Glory."

411
00:13:38,261 --> 00:13:39,930
- "Why did you call me?"
- He didn't watch it.

412
00:13:39,931 --> 00:13:41,130
- "Why..."
- He doesn't know "The Glory."

413
00:13:41,131 --> 00:13:42,670
"Why did you call me in the elevator?"

414
00:13:42,671 --> 00:13:44,200
That reminds me of "New World."

415
00:13:44,201 --> 00:13:45,870
- "All right."
- That's "New World."

416
00:13:45,871 --> 00:13:48,471
- If Moon Dong Eun...
- That reminds me of "Friend."

417
00:13:48,571 --> 00:13:50,410
"We could've met in a room. Why would you..."

418
00:13:50,411 --> 00:13:52,211
- "want to meet me in the elevator?"
- Listen, Ho Dong.

419
00:13:52,411 --> 00:13:54,410
If Moon Dong Eun had been like him,

420
00:13:54,411 --> 00:13:56,581
- no one would've bullied her.
- I thought he was Yu Oh Seong.

421
00:13:56,781 --> 00:14:00,421
- He knows nothing about the drama.
- How can anyone bully her?

422
00:14:01,291 --> 00:14:03,120
Isn't it the scene where you say "Come on in" in the elevator?

423
00:14:03,121 --> 00:14:05,021
- That's from a movie.
- "Come in!"

424
00:14:05,321 --> 00:14:06,861
- "Come in!"
- The famous elevator fight scene...

425
00:14:06,991 --> 00:14:08,660
- From "New World."
- He's so scary.

426
00:14:08,661 --> 00:14:10,200
The transfer form to Men on a Mission.

427
00:14:10,201 --> 00:14:12,501
Names, Jeong Sang Hun, Shin Sung Rok, Kim Gun Woo.

428
00:14:13,031 --> 00:14:15,200
(They're ready to transfer to this school.)

429
00:14:15,201 --> 00:14:18,501
The three guests wrote their nicknames.

430
00:14:18,901 --> 00:14:21,411
First up is Sang Hun. This one is really childish.

431
00:14:22,011 --> 00:14:24,181
Jeong Sang Hun's nickname is "Jeongsang" as in "normal" or "top."

432
00:14:24,981 --> 00:14:26,450
- Sounds like a kid's nickname.
- That's funny.

433
00:14:26,451 --> 00:14:27,680
I think he had many nicknames like that.

434
00:14:27,681 --> 00:14:28,911
- Like "Abnormal Sang Hun."
- "Jeongsang" as in "normal."

435
00:14:29,111 --> 00:14:30,350
You know how kids make nicknames...

436
00:14:30,351 --> 00:14:31,581
- by twisting their friends' names.
- Right. It's simple and funny.

437
00:14:31,851 --> 00:14:33,390
When did you get this nickname?

438
00:14:33,391 --> 00:14:34,590
- It was when I was a little kid.
- Were you in elementary school?

439
00:14:34,591 --> 00:14:36,090
- It must've felt good.
- "Hey, Jeongsang."

440
00:14:36,091 --> 00:14:37,761
"You're the top of the top, Jeongsang."

441
00:14:37,861 --> 00:14:39,590
- "Jeongsang" as in "top?"
- Those who didn't like me...

442
00:14:39,591 --> 00:14:41,490
- called me "Abnormal."  - Right. I thought of that too.

443
00:14:41,491 --> 00:14:42,600
Kids often make nicknames like that.

444
00:14:42,601 --> 00:14:45,901
Those who hated me called me "Jinsang" as in "obnoxious."

445
00:14:46,031 --> 00:14:48,871
My ex-girlfriend called me "Gaejinsang" as in "jerk."

446
00:14:49,171 --> 00:14:51,201
Are you talking about the person we all know?

447
00:14:52,671 --> 00:14:54,310
- He seems to know something.
- There's something.

448
00:14:54,311 --> 00:14:55,910
I guess there was another person at the campsite.

449
00:14:55,911 --> 00:14:57,310
Right. There's no way...

450
00:14:57,311 --> 00:14:58,711
- they went camping by themselves.
- Oh, that's right.

451
00:14:58,811 --> 00:14:59,951
That's not the case.

452
00:15:00,111 --> 00:15:02,050
- It's not? Then what is it?
- I was a jerk.

453
00:15:02,051 --> 00:15:03,621
- It's in the past now.
- Soo Geun is right.

454
00:15:04,221 --> 00:15:07,120
- He looks so serious.
- He shouldn't have said that.

455
00:15:07,121 --> 00:15:08,620
- That was...
- Both of them are flustered.

456
00:15:08,621 --> 00:15:09,890
- Why did you do that, Yeong Cheol?
- Yeong Cheol.

457
00:15:09,891 --> 00:15:12,690
- She's very active now.
- That's right.

458
00:15:12,691 --> 00:15:14,060
- Exactly.
- She's active?

459
00:15:14,061 --> 00:15:16,460
- Why did you date an older woman?
- Is she a TV celebrity?

460
00:15:16,461 --> 00:15:19,030
- Does she not do anything?
- Is she a TV celebrity?

461
00:15:19,031 --> 00:15:20,630
- She does no activities?
- That's not what I mean.

462
00:15:20,631 --> 00:15:21,900
- I mean...
- I thought...

463
00:15:21,901 --> 00:15:23,871
- She must do something.
- She must have her own life.

464
00:15:24,001 --> 00:15:27,470
- She must go for a walk.
- She must be on social media.

465
00:15:27,471 --> 00:15:28,870
- She must do things at home too.
- She's active.

466
00:15:28,871 --> 00:15:30,981
- Going for a walk...
- She must be active somewhere.

467
00:15:31,211 --> 00:15:32,211
- All right.
- This is bad.

468
00:15:32,212 --> 00:15:34,880
I made it funny enough to air.

469
00:15:34,881 --> 00:15:36,780
What do I do? My goodness.

470
00:15:36,781 --> 00:15:40,220
- Back then, I had a temper.
- Right.

471
00:15:40,221 --> 00:15:41,520
And she had a temper too.

472
00:15:41,521 --> 00:15:42,820
We fought every time we met.

473
00:15:42,821 --> 00:15:45,220
And that's why we ended up breaking up.

474
00:15:45,221 --> 00:15:46,830
Stop talking about her. Why would you talk about her?

475
00:15:46,831 --> 00:15:49,661
I want to sugarcoat the story since it will air anyway.

476
00:15:50,761 --> 00:15:52,731
Why don't you know about how TV shows work?

477
00:15:53,001 --> 00:15:54,670
- You're the one who has no idea.
- Or else, I'll regret.

478
00:15:54,671 --> 00:15:56,570
It's obvious that they'll edit out the part where you sugarcoated it.

479
00:15:56,571 --> 00:15:58,870
By the way, she and you... Sang Hun.

480
00:15:58,871 --> 00:15:59,910
If they edit it out...

481
00:15:59,911 --> 00:16:02,440
- Let's move on to Sung Rok.
- Sung Rok.

482
00:16:02,441 --> 00:16:04,111
Sung Rok's nickname is CA.

483
00:16:04,311 --> 00:16:05,340
- "CA?"
- What?

484
00:16:05,341 --> 00:16:08,181
I don't know when, but I started to cry easily.

485
00:16:08,281 --> 00:16:09,950
- What? That doesn't sound like you.
- Oh, that's what it means.

486
00:16:09,951 --> 00:16:12,381
During a table read, a rehearsal,

487
00:16:12,621 --> 00:16:15,120
and a curtain call, I often cry.

488
00:16:15,121 --> 00:16:17,460
At first, my fellow actors said,

489
00:16:17,461 --> 00:16:19,660
"You're very sensitive. And you easily cry."

490
00:16:19,661 --> 00:16:20,831
They thought of it as an admirable trait.

491
00:16:21,131 --> 00:16:23,260
But as it kept happening, they said, "Is he crying again?"

492
00:16:23,261 --> 00:16:24,400
Oh, "CA?"

493
00:16:24,401 --> 00:16:26,000
- "Is he crying again?"
- Do you cry that easily?

494
00:16:26,001 --> 00:16:27,431
- I thought it meant...
- "Is Sung Rok crying again?"

495
00:16:28,171 --> 00:16:30,070
- I thought it meant he was crazy.
- "Is he crying again?"

496
00:16:30,071 --> 00:16:31,441
He's a completely sensitive man.

497
00:16:31,641 --> 00:16:33,910
Sang Hun and Gun Woo, did you see him crying many times?

498
00:16:33,911 --> 00:16:35,540
- I saw him crying so many times.
- Really?

499
00:16:35,541 --> 00:16:37,641
The musical we're playing in has a sad story.

500
00:16:38,141 --> 00:16:41,010
Here's the thing about emotions.

501
00:16:41,011 --> 00:16:44,621
You don't really feel them in all 100 performances.

502
00:16:44,981 --> 00:16:46,591
You get a genuine feeling only in 10 out of 100 performances.

503
00:16:46,821 --> 00:16:48,920
Seeing him stay in the emotion until the very end,

504
00:16:48,921 --> 00:16:51,390
I realized he's either emotional or good at emotional immersion.

505
00:16:51,391 --> 00:16:53,761
- Does he cry every single time?
- Yes, he does.

506
00:16:53,861 --> 00:16:55,631
- Really?
- He's good at emotional immersion.

507
00:16:55,891 --> 00:16:57,830
It's hard to control your voice after crying.

508
00:16:57,831 --> 00:17:00,531
That's right. And that's what worries me as well.

509
00:17:00,771 --> 00:17:04,001
In order to perform the song I sing in the following scene,

510
00:17:04,201 --> 00:17:06,570
maybe I should be less immersed in the emotion.

511
00:17:06,571 --> 00:17:08,670
- Why? Will you play in a musical?
- Will you play in a musical?

512
00:17:08,671 --> 00:17:10,840
- No, that's not why I asked that.
- Do you want to play in a musical?

513
00:17:10,841 --> 00:17:11,880
No, I can't do that.

514
00:17:11,881 --> 00:17:14,710
This is the moment

515
00:17:14,711 --> 00:17:18,350
- Like magic - He wouldn't sing like that.

516
00:17:18,351 --> 00:17:20,691
- He can't use a handheld mic.
- That's okay.

517
00:17:20,821 --> 00:17:23,560
- He can't use a handheld mic.
- But that's okay.

518
00:17:23,561 --> 00:17:24,920
- We put a mic on the forehead.
- They put a mic...

519
00:17:24,921 --> 00:17:26,931
- here on the forehead.
- On the forehead.

520
00:17:26,991 --> 00:17:28,460
- Because sound travels upward, - They place it here.

521
00:17:28,461 --> 00:17:31,160
- musical actors put a mic here.
- On the forehead.

522
00:17:31,161 --> 00:17:32,670
- They don't put it here.
- You can sing with your head voice.

523
00:17:32,671 --> 00:17:34,800
- It captures the resonance well.
- I can't. I'm terrible at dancing.

524
00:17:34,801 --> 00:17:36,271
I'm bad at dancing too.

525
00:17:36,371 --> 00:17:37,470
- He's not good at dancing.
- That's okay.

526
00:17:37,471 --> 00:17:40,140
I must forget everything

527
00:17:40,141 --> 00:17:41,241
You just have to do this move.

528
00:17:41,341 --> 00:17:43,081
As far as I know,

529
00:17:43,511 --> 00:17:45,240
you have another nickname that's more famous than CA.

530
00:17:45,241 --> 00:17:47,250
- That's right.
- I watched "My Love from the Star."

531
00:17:47,251 --> 00:17:48,851
- Oh, right.
- "KakaoTalk Dog."

532
00:17:49,381 --> 00:17:52,351
- That nickname was so popular.
- "KakaoTalk Dog."

533
00:17:52,551 --> 00:17:54,691
- He really looks like the emoji.
- Look at that.

534
00:17:54,891 --> 00:17:57,691
- Shouldn't he receive royalties?
- Exactly.

535
00:17:58,021 --> 00:17:59,190
