- You look like him.

639
00:21:26,161 --> 00:21:28,800
- He totally does.
- That was in the past.

640
00:21:28,801 --> 00:21:31,770
Now, I'm told I look like Lee Seo Jin.

641
00:21:31,771 --> 00:21:34,641
- Yes, I see Seo Jin in his eyes.
- Seo Jin?

642
00:21:34,711 --> 00:21:36,070
- Gun Woo's eyes...
- The eyes.

643
00:21:36,071 --> 00:21:37,611
are like those of Yoo Ji Tae's.

644
00:21:37,641 --> 00:21:39,280
- Wait.
- I've heard that a few times.

645
00:21:39,281 --> 00:21:41,810
- I see it.
- When it comes to Gun Woo,

646
00:21:41,811 --> 00:21:43,720
it's not much now,

647
00:21:43,721 --> 00:21:45,020
but he was so famous...

648
00:21:45,021 --> 00:21:46,250
- as Son Myeong Oh.
- Right.

649
00:21:46,251 --> 00:21:47,950
That's why calling him "Gun Woo" is awkward.

650
00:21:47,951 --> 00:21:50,090
- Actors who lost their names.
- Yes.

651
00:21:50,091 --> 00:21:51,790
Son Myeong Oh and Jeon Jae Jun.

652
00:21:51,791 --> 00:21:53,290
- The role...
- Nobody picked a fight...

653
00:21:53,291 --> 00:21:54,830
with Son Myeong Oh, right?

654
00:21:54,831 --> 00:21:57,960
- No, but I...
- Son Myeong Oh was really evil.

655
00:21:57,961 --> 00:21:59,870
I had hair extensions...

656
00:21:59,871 --> 00:22:02,131
- Right.
- for about six months.

657
00:22:02,171 --> 00:22:05,301
On days I didn't have shoots, I let my hair down.

658
00:22:05,641 --> 00:22:07,940
But people kept their distance from me.

659
00:22:07,941 --> 00:22:09,740
The impression you gave was...

660
00:22:09,741 --> 00:22:11,310
Back then, I had a scary impression.

661
00:22:11,311 --> 00:22:14,181
What surprises me is that, setting aside Sang Hun I'm close with,

662
00:22:14,211 --> 00:22:15,850
Sung Rok and Gun Woo...

663
00:22:15,851 --> 00:22:18,521
- don't give off any villain vibes.
- Exactly.

664
00:22:18,581 --> 00:22:20,251
To be honest, I'm quite disappointed.

665
00:22:20,891 --> 00:22:22,450
You should be a bit evil in real life.

666
00:22:22,451 --> 00:22:23,690
- I would've been like, "It's them."
- Did you think...

667
00:22:23,691 --> 00:22:24,890
we'd show up like this?

668
00:22:24,891 --> 00:22:26,120
Yes, I did.

669
00:22:26,121 --> 00:22:28,061
Here's a dilemma I have.

670
00:22:28,261 --> 00:22:30,500
When I act out a nice character,

671
00:22:30,501 --> 00:22:33,530
the work isn't all that successful.

672
00:22:33,531 --> 00:22:35,300
It's not a big hit.

673
00:22:35,301 --> 00:22:37,440
But act out a villain, and the work hits a jackpot.

674
00:22:37,441 --> 00:22:40,140
- It hits big.
- Fans want to see a villain.

675
00:22:40,141 --> 00:22:42,841
But I want to play a nice character after all those villains,

676
00:22:43,081 --> 00:22:45,910
but after experiencing that trend, I can't muster the courage...

677
00:22:45,911 --> 00:22:47,851
