- Because it's your first time.

697
00:23:32,561 --> 00:23:33,561
Right.

698
00:23:33,562 --> 00:23:35,560
The air he gives off is different.

699
00:23:35,561 --> 00:23:37,031
I'm dead scared right now.

700
00:23:37,061 --> 00:23:38,760
- I don't blame you.
- He's no joke, right?

701
00:23:38,761 --> 00:23:42,071
The current Ho Dong is quite docile compared to before, right?

702
00:23:42,201 --> 00:23:43,341
- Next.
- Okay.

703
00:23:43,771 --> 00:23:45,600
This is a first in history.

704
00:23:45,601 --> 00:23:47,210
The students were asked about their educational background.

705
00:23:47,211 --> 00:23:48,211
- They must have...
- We rarely...

706
00:23:48,212 --> 00:23:49,341
- a good educational background.
- ask for it.

707
00:23:49,441 --> 00:23:51,180
First off, Sang Hun.

708
00:23:51,181 --> 00:23:52,181
Broadcasting and Entertainment Department,

709
00:23:52,181 --> 00:23:53,181
Seoul Institute of the Arts.

710
00:23:53,182 --> 00:23:55,011
- You son of a...
- What?

711
00:23:55,651 --> 00:23:57,520
Forget it. You didn't graduate.

712
00:23:57,521 --> 00:23:59,120
- Come on.
- When did you enter school?

713
00:23:59,121 --> 00:24:00,651
- I entered in 1996.
- What?

714
00:24:00,791 --> 00:24:02,750
- I entered in 1996.
- Same here.

715
00:24:02,751 --> 00:24:04,090
- What?
- Sang Min isn't a senior.

716
00:24:04,091 --> 00:24:05,691
We're classmates, you son of a...

717
00:24:06,561 --> 00:24:08,830
Classmates don't threaten others, you son of a...

718
00:24:08,831 --> 00:24:10,301
- Why don't you two know each other?
- They don't?

719
00:24:10,401 --> 00:24:11,661
I was in the Film Department.

720
00:24:11,961 --> 00:24:13,931
That's not even our department, you son of a...

721
00:24:14,031 --> 00:24:15,930
- Here's what matters.
- Okay.

722
00:24:15,931 --> 00:24:17,571
Have you two met at school?

723
00:24:17,901 --> 00:24:19,540
- Not even once.
- He dropped out.

724
00:24:19,541 --> 00:24:21,810
Nobody can confirm his educational background.

725
00:24:21,811 --> 00:24:24,240
- Back then, I was active.
- Roo'Ra.

726
00:24:24,241 --> 00:24:25,610
I was in Roo'Ra back then.

727
00:24:25,611 --> 00:24:28,450
I was the top male student.

728
00:24:28,451 --> 00:24:30,180
- Top for what?
- Was there a division?

729
00:24:30,181 --> 00:24:31,820
- The top student?
- I was good in the practical test.

730
00:24:31,821 --> 00:24:33,390
Sang Min claims he attended that school...

731
00:24:33,391 --> 00:24:35,491
- I never bumped into him.
- and was even on the news.

732
00:24:35,691 --> 00:24:37,660
- But nobody saw him.
- I didn't either.

733
00:24:37,661 --> 00:24:39,290
When I heard Lee Sang Min of Roo'Ra was in school,

734
00:24:39,291 --> 00:24:40,460
- he wasn't there.
- It was in the newspaper.

735
00:24:40,461 --> 00:24:42,490
Didn't you drop out when you were a freshman, Sang Min?

736
00:24:42,491 --> 00:24:43,960
- Exactly.
- In freshman year.

737
00:24:43,961 --> 00:24:45,400
- Did you graduate, Sang Hun?
- Top student.

738
00:24:45,401 --> 00:24:46,430
- Me?
- Yes.

739
00:24:46,431 --> 00:24:47,470
Amazing.

740
00:24:47,471 --> 00:24:48,930
I repeated freshman year twice.

741
00:24:48,931 --> 00:24:50,471
- Okay.
- But in the end...

742
00:24:50,541 --> 00:24:52,440
- Did you drop out of school?
- I did.

743
00:24:52,441 --> 00:24:54,270
- But why did you write that down?
- I...

744
00:24:54,271 --> 00:24:56,110
I dropped out. I quit school.

745
00:24:56,111 --> 00:24:57,380
- What? I did too.
- I quit school.

746
00:24:57,381 --> 00:24:58,780
No offense or anything,

747
00:24:58,781 --> 00:25:00,911
but why won't you two say you only have a high school diploma?

748
00:25:01,181 --> 00:25:02,480
Why did you write Seoul Institute of the Arts...

749
00:25:02,481 --> 00:25:04,150
in your educational background?

750
00:25:04,151 --> 00:25:05,480
- Exactly.
- That's wrong.

751
00:25:05,481 --> 00:25:07,551
What about those who graduated after paying all the tuition fees?

752
00:25:07,591 --> 00:25:09,320
What about them? Can you attend the alumni party?

753
00:25:09,321 --> 00:25:10,591
- Dropping out...
- You can't, right?

754
00:25:10,921 --> 00:25:12,190
- Aren't I right?
- Seoul Institute of the Arts...

755
00:25:12,191 --> 00:25:13,260
might hate it.

756
00:25:13,261 --> 00:25:14,360
- Exactly.
- Who knows?

757
00:25:14,361 --> 00:25:16,290
But I even went to the festival.

758
00:25:16,291 --> 00:25:18,301
Even non-students can go to the festival.

759
00:25:18,931 --> 00:25:19,931
- Right.
- I went to...

760
00:25:19,931 --> 00:25:20,931
Yonsei University's festival...

761
00:25:20,932 --> 00:25:21,970
- Exactly.
- even though I didn't attend...

762
00:25:21,971 --> 00:25:22,971
Yonsei.

763
00:25:23,031 --> 00:25:24,940
Who did you hang out with back then, Sang Hun?

764
00:25:24,941 --> 00:25:26,610
I hung out with many guys.

765
00:25:26,611 --> 00:25:27,640
Boast about your classmates.

766
00:25:27,641 --> 00:25:29,471
Who is active right now among your classmates?

767
00:25:29,511 --> 00:25:31,710
Cha Tae Hyun, who entered a year early.

768
00:25:31,711 --> 00:25:33,510
- Tae Hyun.
- And?

769
00:25:33,511 --> 00:25:36,311
And among those who entered with me...

770
00:25:36,651 --> 00:25:39,851
Among my classmates... What was his name again?

771
00:25:40,191 --> 00:25:41,850
- What is with you?
- Come on.

772
00:25:41,851 --> 00:25:44,260
- What?
- You...

773
00:25:44,261 --> 00:25:46,390
- The one in...
- Let's move on.

774
00:25:46,391 --> 00:25:48,430
Sung Rok. I see.

775
00:25:48,431 --> 00:25:51,700
Sung Rok was a Theater and Film major at the University of Suwon.

776
00:25:51,701 --> 00:25:54,401
- It's a four-year college.
- Yes.

777
00:25:54,571 --> 00:25:55,701
Did you not drop out?

778
00:25:56,131 --> 00:25:57,171
Did you graduate from the school?

779
00:25:57,901 --> 00:25:59,800
You also only have a high school diploma.

780
00:25:59,801 --> 00:26:02,211
- Really.
- What is up with these guys?

781
00:26:02,641 --> 00:26:04,010
- Hey.
- Come on.

782
00:26:04,011 --> 00:26:05,880
Having only a high school diploma isn't embarrassing.

783
00:26:05,881 --> 00:26:07,210
- Why bring up college?
- Really.

784
00:26:07,211 --> 00:26:08,510
Having only a high school diploma isn't embarrassing.

785
00:26:08,511 --> 00:26:10,220
- Exactly.
- Why write your college down?

786
00:26:10,221 --> 00:26:12,250
- Listen.
- Even he didn't graduate.

787
00:26:12,251 --> 00:26:13,251
Don't get the wrong idea.

788
00:26:13,252 --> 00:26:14,890
Anyone could write a college down.

789
00:26:14,891 --> 00:26:16,190
- Only those who dropped out know.
- Is it embarrassing?

790
00:26:16,191 --> 00:26:17,320
A high school diploma isn't embarrassing.

791
00:26:17,321 --> 00:26:19,290
To say that I only have a high school diploma,

792
00:26:19,291 --> 00:26:21,890
I attended college, which feels wrong not to talk about.

793
00:26:21,891 --> 00:26:22,960
- True.
- Of course.

794
00:26:22,961 --> 00:26:24,300
I attended for two years.

795
00:26:24,301 --> 00:26:25,930
Anyone would think...

796
00:26:25,931 --> 00:26:27,601
- you graduated from college.
- Exactly.

797
00:26:27,871 --> 00:26:28,900
But since you dropped out,

798
00:26:28,901 --> 00:26:30,370
- we feel betrayed.
- Yes.

799
00:26:30,371 --> 00:26:32,670
- That's the point.
- The betrayal is...

800
00:26:32,671 --> 00:26:34,811
Anyone would think I dropped out of college.

801
00:26:34,871 --> 00:26:36,710
- Sung Rok...
- Sung Rok didn't say a thing.

802
00:26:36,711 --> 00:26:39,780
- Exactly.
- No offense, Sung Rok.

803
00:26:39,781 --> 00:26:41,910
- Yes?
- Everyone here...

804
00:26:41,911 --> 00:26:44,020
dropped out of college.

805
00:26:44,021 --> 00:26:45,481
- Really?
- Everyone...

806
00:26:45,681 --> 00:26:46,820
We're all the same.

807
00:26:46,821 --> 00:26:48,990
Which high school did you graduate from?

808
00:26:48,991 --> 00:26:51,521
High school-wise, I'm Jang Hoon's junior.

809
00:26:51,621 --> 00:26:52,891
- Whimoon High School?
- Whimoon High School?

810
00:26:53,021 --> 00:26:55,290
I attended the same high school...

811
00:26:55,291 --> 00:26:56,560
and was a basketball player.

812
00:26:56,561 --> 00:26:58,530
- What?
- An actual athlete?

813
00:26:58,531 --> 00:26:59,970
I was in Whimoon Middle and High School's basketball team.

814
00:26:59,971 --> 00:27:01,770
- For real?
- He's Jang Hoon's junior.

815
00:27:01,771 --> 00:27:03,130
An elite player, not as a hobbyist?

816
00:27:03,131 --> 00:27:04,500
An elite.

817
00:27:04,501 --> 00:27:05,640
Why did you quit?

818
00:27:05,641 --> 00:27:08,641
- After getting injured and such, - Yes?

819
00:27:08,741 --> 00:27:12,110
I realized I wouldn't succeed as a basketball player.

820
00:27:12,111 --> 00:27:13,850
- With that, I changed my path.
- But...

821
00:27:13,851 --> 00:27:15,910
Record holder Seo Jang Hoon...

822
00:27:15,911 --> 00:27:17,150
doesn't acknowledge injuries.

823
00:27:17,151 --> 00:27:18,480
- No, he doesn't.
- If...

824
00:27:18,481 --> 00:27:20,751
you're the ace, your team must make you...

825
00:27:20,851 --> 00:27:22,820
fix it one way or another...

826
00:27:22,821 --> 00:27:23,990
- Fix.
- and play for the team.

827
00:27:23,991 --> 00:27:26,291
- Correct.
- What do you think about that?

828
00:27:26,391 --> 00:27:27,590
Where did you get hurt?

829
00:27:27,591 --> 00:27:29,661
I had a lumbar disc surgery.

830
00:27:30,331 --> 00:27:31,901
- Isn't that...
- No.

831
00:27:32,161 --> 00:27:34,271
Fix it one way or another.

832
00:27:35,371 --> 00:27:38,201
How do you play with a herniated disc?

833
00:27:38,371 --> 00:27:39,470
Hey.

834
00:27:39,471 --> 00:27:40,970
How do you play with a herniated disc?

835
00:27:40,971 --> 00:27:42,110
If you're the ace.

836
00:27:42,111 --> 00:27:44,441
I have had a herniated disc since college.

837
00:27:44,611 --> 00:27:47,511
If the team needs you,

838
00:27:47,751 --> 00:27:49,750
- True.
- you have to play...

839
00:27:49,751 --> 00:27:52,080
- Yes.
- by fixing your problem...

840
00:27:52,081 --> 00:27:53,690
- in one way or another.
- He'd ask a noted doctor to fix it.

841
00:27:53,691 --> 00:27:55,020
- Even with a limp?
- No.

842
00:27:55,021 --> 00:27:56,290
You'd fix it.

843
00:27:56,291 --> 00:27:58,320
Was it bad to the point you had a limp?

844
00:27:58,321 --> 00:27:59,990
I was limping, and my disc was out of place.

845
00:27:59,991 --> 00:28:01,190
- So...
- I had to have surgery.

846
00:28:01,191 --> 00:28:03,230
When you said you were quitting,

847
00:28:03,231 --> 00:28:05,901
how did the coach react?

848
00:28:06,101 --> 00:28:07,130
He didn't stop me.

849
00:28:07,131 --> 00:28:08,671
- He didn't?
- Why not?

850
00:28:09,101 --> 00:28:11,170
Well, as he said,

851
00:28:11,171 --> 00:28:13,240
if I were needed, I would've been fixed.

852
00:28:13,241 --> 00:28:14,970
But he accepted my request because I wasn't needed.

853
00:28:14,971 --> 00:28:18,211
- Right.
- Sung Rok played basketball,

854
00:28:18,611 --> 00:28:20,450
but his younger brother...

855
00:28:20,451 --> 00:28:21,950
even played as a professional basketball player.

856
00:28:21,951 --> 00:28:22,980
Really?

857
00:28:22,981 --> 00:28:24,980
- His name is Shin Jae Rok.
- Shin Jae Rok.

858
00:28:24,981 --> 00:28:26,920
He graduated from Whimoon High School.

859
00:28:26,921 --> 00:28:28,350
Everyone played basketball.

860
00:28:28,351 --> 00:28:31,061
What was the best score you made as a basketball player?

861
00:28:31,391 --> 00:28:32,391
- Me?
- Yes.

862
00:28:32,392 --> 00:28:33,630
- Before your herniated disc.
- Well...

863
00:28:33,631 --> 00:28:34,930
- Did you make a double-digit score?
- Before your surgery.

864
00:28:34,931 --> 00:28:36,290
I scored over 20 and such.

865
00:28:36,291 --> 00:28:37,960
- If he scored over 20...
- Over 20 is...

866
00:28:37,961 --> 00:28:39,130
Do you have proof?

867
00:28:39,131 --> 00:28:41,131
I don't. But listen.

868
00:28:41,201 --> 00:28:42,670
We had a celebrity...

869
00:28:42,671 --> 00:28:44,500
- basketball tournament.
- I remember.

870
00:28:44,501 --> 00:28:46,670
I took part in the early days.

871
00:28:46,671 --> 00:28:48,370
Of course, I was a former player.

872
00:28:48,371 --> 00:28:49,911
But I was the MVP.

873
00:28:50,381 --> 00:28:52,740
- You were the...
- I'm sure we have pictures.

874
00:28:52,741 --> 00:28:55,310
Were you in "Handsome Tigers?"

875
00:28:55,311 --> 00:28:56,980
Why didn't you join?

876
00:28:56,981 --> 00:28:58,820
Why didn't you invite me, Jang Hoon?

877
00:28:58,821 --> 00:29:01,190
- I know.
- You said you would do it again.

878
00:29:01,191 --> 00:29:02,650
- Jang Hoon must have thought, - You said...

879
00:29:02,651 --> 00:29:04,860
"Sung Rok isn't handsome at all."

880
00:29:04,861 --> 00:29:06,460
You both went to...

881
00:29:06,461 --> 00:29:07,631
- Whimoon High School.
- I just...

882
00:29:07,931 --> 00:29:10,330
Well, it's that...

883
00:29:10,331 --> 00:29:12,400
- This is going to take a while.
- Tell us.

884
00:29:12,401 --> 00:29:14,830
- It's okay.
- Make it short.

885
00:29:14,831 --> 00:29:16,000
- Let me just...
- That was polite.

886
00:29:16,001 --> 00:29:17,500
- "I beg your pardon for it."
- Let me just...

887
00:29:17,501 --> 00:29:20,210
ask for permission from this guy.

888
00:29:20,211 --> 00:29:23,380
Don't say that it's going to be long before you actually start.

889
00:29:23,381 --> 00:29:25,840
For "Handsome Tigers,"

890
00:29:25,841 --> 00:29:29,310
we agreed that we wouldn't pick anyone who played professionally.

891
00:29:29,311 --> 00:29:30,520
- Since he played professionally?
- He did.

892
00:29:30,521 --> 00:29:32,620
- No one played professionally.
- For "Passionate Basketball Team,"

893
00:29:32,621 --> 00:29:37,261
I'm sure the staff contacted him,

894
00:29:37,691 --> 00:29:39,360
- but his agency...
- Declined?

895
00:29:39,361 --> 00:29:43,500
said that he had plans for a musical and other things,

896
00:29:43,501 --> 00:29:46,560
so they declined earlier on.

897
00:29:46,561 --> 00:29:49,370
- But if you really had needed him, - Is it what you said?

898
00:29:49,371 --> 00:29:51,570
I'm sure Jang Hoon would have gone to him directly.

899
00:29:51,571 --> 00:29:53,240
- No, but...
- If he needed you.

900
00:29:53,241 --> 00:29:54,510
no matter how much I need him,

901
00:29:54,511 --> 00:29:57,611
I can't do anything about his schedule.

902
00:29:57,981 --> 00:29:59,011
Next.

903
00:29:59,511 --> 00:30:03,111
Gun Woo went to Korea National University of Arts...

904
00:30:03,551 --> 00:30:06,180
- and majored in acting.
- Gosh.

905
00:30:06,181 --> 00:30:07,790
Did you graduate?

906
00:30:07,791 --> 00:30:09,320
- Korea National University of Arts.
- What about you?

907
00:30:09,321 --> 00:30:11,660
- I only made it to the second year.
- What?

908
00:30:11,661 --> 00:30:13,930
- What?
- Up to the second year?

909
00:30:13,931 --> 00:30:15,890
- Why are you all like that?
- I trusted you.

910
00:30:15,891 --> 00:30:17,860
- That's too bad.
- It's such a good school.

911
00:30:17,861 --> 00:30:19,200
- I'm sorry, but...
- Hey.

912
00:30:19,201 --> 00:30:21,430
- is there anyone who graduated?
- Hey.

913
00:30:21,431 --> 00:30:23,470
You can be the captain,

914
00:30:23,471 --> 00:30:25,200
and we should make a dropout group.

915
00:30:25,201 --> 00:30:26,700
Come to this side.

916
00:30:26,701 --> 00:30:28,110
Why did you all drop out?

917
00:30:28,111 --> 00:30:29,210
- Come this way if you dropped out.
- Hey.

918
00:30:29,211 --> 00:30:31,180
- Come over here.
- It's this way.

919
00:30:31,181 --> 00:30:32,340
Dropouts here.

920
00:30:32,341 --> 00:30:33,951
- You went there.
- I dropped out.

921
00:30:34,381 --> 00:30:36,210
This way.

922
00:30:36,211 --> 00:30:37,750
- I dropped out.
- I'm a high school graduate.

923
00:30:37,751 --> 00:30:38,850
- I dropped out.
- I'm a high school graduate.

924
00:30:38,851 --> 00:30:40,220
- Did you graduate?
- Hey.

925
00:30:40,221 --> 00:30:41,750
- You high school graduates.
- How frustrating.

926
00:30:41,751 --> 00:30:44,160
- Stop talking about your school.
- I know.

927
00:30:44,161 --> 00:30:45,590
You shouldn't mention it.

928
00:30:45,591 --> 00:30:48,160
Gun Woo, who did you go to school with?

929
00:30:48,161 --> 00:30:49,260
- There are a lot.
- My peers?

930
00:30:49,261 --> 00:30:51,260
Those who are active these days include...

931
00:30:51,261 --> 00:30:52,700
a guy called Yang Se Jong.

932
00:30:52,701 --> 00:30:54,031
- Yang Se Jong.
- Yes.

933
00:30:54,371 --> 00:30:55,471
Did Se Jong graduate?

934
00:30:56,401 --> 00:30:58,840
- Hey. Come on.
- Why are you all...

935
00:30:58,841 --> 00:31:00,470
They become actors right away.

936
00:31:00,471 --> 00:31:03,270
- You became actors right away.
- They are talented.

937
00:31:03,271 --> 00:31:04,940
Korea National University of Arts...

938
00:31:04,941 --> 00:31:06,880
- They won't leave you alone.
- is really tough to get into.

939
00:31:06,881 --> 00:31:09,080
- Yes.
- When it comes to acting,

940
00:31:09,081 --> 00:31:11,380
Seoul Institute of the Arts and Korea National University of Arts...

941
00:31:11,381 --> 00:31:13,350
- are really tough to get into.
- And you need good grades...

942
00:31:13,351 --> 00:31:14,390
to get into Korea National University of Arts.

943
00:31:14,391 --> 00:31:15,391
- I'm sorry, but...
- Did you go there?

944
00:31:15,392 --> 00:31:16,620
Wait a minute.

945
00:31:16,621 --> 00:31:18,020
I'm sorry, but why are you leaving out the University of Suwon?

946
00:31:18,021 --> 00:31:20,190
- That's right. I forgot.
- I'm sorry, but...

947
00:31:20,191 --> 00:31:21,530
You didn't even graduate from there.

948
00:31:21,531 --> 00:31:22,890
You still need to include it.

949
00:31:22,891 --> 00:31:26,560
But I heard that Gun Woo got in with the top scores.

950
00:31:26,561 --> 00:31:27,570
- Really?
- That's right.

951
00:31:27,571 --> 00:31:29,400
- You got in with the top scores?
- He is...

952
00:31:29,401 --> 00:31:31,070
You all got in well.

953
